{
  "explanation": "The defendant abused a professional position of trust inherent to their role as an accountant to misappropriate $25,000 for personal use. While the lack of a prior criminal history and the partial restitution of the stolen funds serve as significant mitigating factors that warrant a degree of leniency, the intentional nature of the breach of fiduciary duty necessitates a period of incarceration to provide adequate punishment and deter similar conduct. A four-month term reflects the seriousness of the offense while acknowledging the defendant's efforts to rectify the harm caused.",
  "verdict": 4
}
